<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-03-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="404" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4960/8.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Leishman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-03-15"><hi rend="italic">March 15,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 163.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch of the 22d ultimo, reporting your interview with the Sultan on
                            the same day, regarding equal treatment of American institutions, and
                            stating that <pb facs="1201" n="1051" xml:id="pg_1051"/> if further
                            obstacles to the fulfillment of His Majesty’s promises arise you will
                            ask the department for further instructions.</p>
                        <p>In view of the telegrams exchanged March 5 and 6, the department will
                            await the result of your request for another audience of His
                            Majesty.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>(See also correspondence, Increase of Turkish Customs Duties,
                                following.)</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>